org.eng.aisp.processor

Interface IWindowProcessor<WINDOW extends IDataWindow<?>,RESULT>

  • Type Parameters:
    WINDOW - the specific type of IDataWindow on which #apply(Object) will be called.
    RESULT - the output of the #apply(Object) method.
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    IDoubleFeatureExtractor, IFeatureExtractor<WINDATA,FDATA>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractCachingWindowProcessor, FFTFeatureExtractor, IdentityFeatureExtractor, LogMelFeatureExtractor, MFCCFeatureExtractor, MFFBFeatureExtractor, MultiDimensionFeatureExtractor, RMSFeatureExtractor, StatsFeatureExtractor

    public interface IWindowProcessor<WINDOW extends IDataWindow<?>,RESULT>
    A generic interface that provides an #apply(Object) method that operations on a IDataWindow to produce a result.
